radiographic_examinations.findings: Stanford type B aortic dissection with periaortic hematoma, hemorrhagic pleural effusion, and atelectatic lungs.
Sealing of the false lumen without malperfusion of the visceral vessels.
Distal part of the endograft was located in the false lumen of the descending aorta.
Good positioning of the stent graft, bare stents, and coils, with normal blood flow to the aorta, patent visceral artery, and vanished false lumen.
The false lumen completely disappeared without clinical or surgical complications.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Complete disappearance of the false lumen.
